To install esphome, do this:

git clone https://github.com/esphome/esphome.git
cd esphome
git checkout dev
./script/setup

To use esphome from the command line, activate the python
virtual environment like this:

source venv/bin/activate

and the you can cd into the growOS/esp/cpu0 directory and do this:

esphome compile boot.yaml
esphome upload boot.yaml
esphome logs boot.yaml

or do all three in one shot using this command:

esphome run boot.yaml

Note that you should probably change the boot.yaml wifi: config
to something that is on KoningNet.  I recommend manual config for
the IP address not DHCP for development since the target will boot faster.
Perhaps choose something like 192.168.248.10, which is outside the
KoningNet DHCP range.

Let me know if it works for you!


